The paper focuses on designing combinatorial algorithms for the Capacitated Network Design problem, which is a problem in network optimization. This makes it likely to belong to the cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of submodular functions, which are commonly studied in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the Group Steiner tree problem and the Connected Facility Location problem, which are both problems in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper mentions approximation algorithms, which are commonly studied in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
